   'Situation: I was up for a promotion at work and did not receive it.\nDistorted Thought: I will be stuck in middle-management for the remainder of my career.\nRational Response: I did not receive this promotion, but I do good work and hopefully, I will be promoted in the future.',
   'Situation: I run a business with my close friend and we were taking work-related photos at their house. I took the memory card home but lost it while I was walking.\nDistorted Thought: My friend is going to be angry with me\nRational Response: I do not know how my friend will react, and I should not assume.',
   "Situation: I confronted a coworker about eating my food from the refrigerator, only to realize the custodians threw away my food the night before.\nDistorted Thought: My coworkers are making fun of me now\nRational Response: I don't know what my coworkers are thinking but they likely have more going on today than thinking about these conversations we had earlier.",
   "Situation: Fired for not meeting quota as a salesman.\nDistorted Thought: I can't pay my bills.\nRational Response: I feel bad for getting fired and it makes me scared about my financial future. I have gotten through other hard things and can get through this hard thing too.",
   'Situation: Our forest inventory data is due in less than three days and I still have over 100 plots to do.  The date cannot be missed and my superiors expect it completed.\nDistorted Thought: I have at least four normal days of plot work needing done in three days\nRational Response: I have a lot of work to do and this deadline is important to me. I should discuss this with my supervisors to see if I can get any help with this project.',
   'Situation: I left a toxic job that abused me for 12 years. I thought I found a new job that was better, but realized they lied to me about the job and now I hate working here. I feel like I made a huge mistake.\nDistorted Thought: I can never get a break. Every time I try to make a positive change in my life, something happens to ruin it.\nRational Response: I have received a number of breaks in life that greatly improved my current circumstances.  Using "never" is an extreme belief.',
   'Situation: I did a poor job organizing a meeting, but it turned out to not be a big deal.\nDistorted Thought: I am not a good project manager.\nRational Response: I hold high expectations of myself, and in this case I did not meet them. Even so, the meeting went well. Maybe my expectations are too high and I do not need to try as hard as I previously thought going forward. I should discuss this with my supervisor about how best to prioritize my time and figure out what they expect of me.',
   "Situation: I failed to do a work task appropriately in a side-gig.\nDistorted Thought: I won't get paid\nRational Response: I made a mistake this time because I am stretched too thin. Next time I will allocate more time to my side gig so it doesn't get messed up again.",
   'Situation: I mixed up the addresses on two packages and sent them to the wrong place\nDistorted Thought: I screwed up again at work\nRational Response: I made a mistake, and it happens to everyone. I should not be too hard on myself.',
   "Situation: I made a mistake with an expensive reagent at work and ruined my experiment.\nDistorted Thought: I'm mad at myself for being careless\nRational Response: I made a mistake, and mistakes happen to everyone. That doesn't mean I am being careless.",
   "Situation: I was called into a meeting with my boss where I was told that I wasn't meeting the standards at work.\nDistorted Thought: I am not doing well enough to warrant working at this job.\nRational Response: I need to work harder to meet the standards but my boss was willing to talk with me about this because he is committed to my improvement",
   "Situation: I had a complaint against my work which I felt unnecessary to bring to my attention as it was very minor.\nDistorted Thought: There was no need to even say anything it was very minor.\nRational Response: I want to look at some of the positive aspects of my work in addition to this minor complaint.  I know that I'm doing the best I can, which includes triumphs and mistakes.",
   'Situation: While I was at work, my supervisor questioned my decision in a negative tone infront of my peers.\nDistorted Thought: She needs to stop discussing this.\nRational Response: I was embarrassed and I should give my boss feedback that I was feeling defensive. Hopefully we can resolve this in the future.',
   'Situation: Our forest inventory data is due in less than three days and I still have over 100 plots to do.  The date cannot be missed and my superiors expect it completed.\nDistorted Thought: I have at least four normal days of plot work needing done in three days\nRational Response: I will do my best to get the work done, and I trust that my supervisor will be reasonable if I cannot meet the deadline.',
   "Situation: I'm waiting everyday for the weekend and the holidays. I'm not getting anything productive done.\nDistorted Thought: I can't bring myself to be motivated.\nRational Response: If I'm waiting everyday for the weekend and the holidays, that may not be my fault. My job may be unsatisfying/unfulfilling.",
   "Situation: Fired for not meeting quota as a salesman.\nDistorted Thought: I can't pay my bills.\nRational Response: I'm feeling anxious about losing that job. I will have to be careful with my spending and work efficiently to find a new way to ensure that I can pay my bills.",
   "Situation: My boss yelled at me\nDistorted Thought: I'm feeling sad\nRational Response: It doesn't feel good to be yelled at. I can focus on what I can control about the situation and let go of what I can't control.",
   'Situation: I do gas stations audits and I messed up and forgot something I was supposed to do\nDistorted Thought: I felt like a failure and am ashamed I made this mistake\nRational Response: It makes sense I am ashamed about this mistake. I will fix it.',
   "Situation: I confronted a coworker about eating my food from the refrigerator, only to realize the custodians threw away my food the night before.\nDistorted Thought: My coworkers are making fun of me now\nRational Response: It was an accident and misunderstanding. I can't let this take up my entire day. I will just apologize and move on.",
   "Situation: For many years I've been tutoring students online in math and reading. One of my newer students requested to my supervisor that she be assigned to a different tutor because she didn't like me.\nDistorted Thought: I was searching my brain to figure out why she didn't like me, and it made me so sad to think I'd hurt her feelings or caused a problem for her.\nRational Response: it's ok if people dont like me",
   "Situation: My boss yelled at me\nDistorted Thought: I'm feeling sad\nRational Response: It's okay to feel sad when being yelled at. I will get through this",
   "Situation: I failed to do a work task appropriately in a side-gig.\nDistorted Thought: I won't get paid\nRational Response: Just because I made some mistakes doesn't mean I won't be able to fix them and still get paid. I need to check back in to see what can be done to fix this.",
   'Situation: I tried to advertise my business more but have gotten zero leads from it.\nDistorted Thought: I am not good at what I do.\nRational Response: My advertising has not reached my ideal customers, I might need to try a different strategy. I wonder who could help me out with advertising?',
