   "Situation: My girlfriend was ignoring me for a while.\nDistorted Thought: She didn't like me anymore.\nRational Response: If my girlfriend doesn't like me anymore, I trust that she will tell me that and not just ignore me. Guessing at what others are thinking is not fair to either one of us.",
   "Situation: My boyfriend and I were supposed to go out last night and I got very aggravated at the change of plans and that he pushed back the time.\nDistorted Thought: he didn't respect our initial commitment\nRational Response: it makes sense that i was aggravated because of the changes. it doesnt mean he doesnt respect our initial commitment. something might have come up",
   "Situation: My boyfriend and I were supposed to go out last night and I got very aggravated at the change of plans and that he pushed back the time.\nDistorted Thought: he didn't respect our initial commitment\nRational Response: my boyfriend respects our commitment. something probably came up",
   "Situation: I am quite fond of a coworker and decide to talk to them. I offer up the idea that it might be fun to go out together sometime, and they respond with the fact they are too busy.\nDistorted Thought: I'm not attractive or have a good enough personality.\nRational Response: My feeling are hurt after getting rejected like that. It could be true that they are too busy or maybe there are other reasons they don't want to go out with me. I can't know for sure but I will get over this and find a good match for me.",
   "Situation: My girlfriend was ignoring me for a while.\nDistorted Thought: She didn't like me anymore.\nRational Response: My girlfriend has not responded, but I should be patient and not jump to conclusions about what this means until I talk to her",
   "Situation: My husband and his friends are always speaking Spanish in front of me and I cannot understand anything\nDistorted Thought: they are saying things in front of me that they don't want me to know or understand\nRational Response: My husband is trustworthy and would not be deceitful towards me",
   "Situation: My husband wants a divorce, I've self isolated for years, my brother died\nDistorted Thought: Worthlessness, abandonment, grief\nRational Response: My husband's reasons for wanting a divorce do not mean I am worthless.",
   "Situation: I had a disagreement about our finances with my partner at our home about a week ago that caused her to leave the apartment and not talk, call, or text me for hours.\nDistorted Thought: I worried that she might break up with me and that I'd never see her again.\nRational Response: My partner is upset and needed space after an argument, it is okay that we process things in different ways. I trust that we will try to resolve this once we have both calmed down",
